Magnus Clyde.title: Dusk (Rework) · Rise n' Set
Magnus Clyde.about:
Rise & Set are albums in tribute to The Caretaker as well as its community, and is the final version of what was Dusk, and what we wanted to portray in it.
Rise & Set, representing the time-of-day, is an artistic representation of the effects of sundowning with early Alzheimer's, and the distortions of the memories and self as a result. Many sleepless nights distort and disrupt recollection, and serve to further worsen one's condition. Something is brewing behind the scenes.

I · "Twenty thousand sunrises"
(A-B) Clinical Stage I / II
Of course, we all get old. Why not stop and smell the roses?
"Within the stars, all feels like one" · PhiSigma, 2022
-----
II · "For we all stood to wait"
(C-D) Clinical Stage II
Our wonderful little garden is doing well. Some flowers wilt, but many take their place.
"The few become the many, the Sun begins to set" · PhiSigma, 2022
-----
III · "The looming storms dim the skies"
(E-F) Clinical Stage II / III
It's bitterly cold, isn't it? And yet, last I'd checked it was August.
"Out past the clouds, the night sky glows" · PhiSigma, 2022
-----
IV · "And the minutes began to flake"
(G-H) Clinical Stage III / IV
We hardly see you around anymore.
"As all begins to melt away, the dead of night approaches." · PhiSigma, 2022
-----
V · "I began to see demise"
(I-J) Clinical Stage IV / V
Nothing's planted, I don't have a thing in the ground.
